nalText":"Workers Plane","height":35,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#846358","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":2111284324,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":6,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":553.92460317460234,"angle":0,"y":2102.7777777777778,"width":187.06666564941406},{"seed":638596856,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"RouxEFG_Vf6aVywZ7hOYY","strokeWidth":4,"roughness":0,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":28,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1780856050275,"locked":false,"text":"Design a framework that automatically generates and manages standardised, version-controlled CI\/CD\npipelines for microservices at scale. You may assume any CI\/CD engine of your choice. Also explain the\npipeline structure itself — stages, quality gates, validations, environment promotion, and configuration\nmanagement across regions. Propose strategies to minimize deployment downtime and rollback risk.","version":285,"autoResize":false,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"#ffffff","index":"bmy","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Design a framework that automatically generates and manages standardised, version-controlled CI\/CD pipelines for microservices at scale. You may assume any CI\/CD engine of your choice. Also explain the pipeline structure itself — stages, quality gates, validations, environment promotion, and configuration management across regions. Propose strategies to minimize deployment downtime and rollback risk.","height":140,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":674120668,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":6,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":687.19760940154356,"angle":0,"y":-828.71084249205194,"width":1395.110694803891},{"seed":583058312,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"aMOcp22UPJ_gfMUZbaJ2n","strokeWidth":4,"roughness":0,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":28,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1780856050275,"locked":false,"text":"Constraints\n- 500 engineers\n- 300 services\n- Builds\/days: 5 000 builds\/day\n- Concurrent builds: 125\n- Worker nodes = 50 (4 GB RAM jobs for  64 GB vm)\n- 700 deployments\/day","version":510,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"#ffffff","index":"bmz","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Constraints\n- 500 engineers\n- 300 services\n- Builds\/days: 5 000 builds\/day\n- Concurrent builds: 125\n- Worker nodes = 50 (4 GB RAM jobs for  64 GB vm)\n- 700 deployments\/day","height":245,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1806530532,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":6,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":2309.8591269841272,"angle":0,"y":-388.37698412698398,"width":664.74786376953125},{"seed":927235832,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"CXp5FCyxpoMJTjYIW_IBD","strokeWidth":4,"roughness":0,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":28,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1780856050275,"locked":false,"text":"Requirements\n- Engineers want to ship their code to production (building, testing, deploying)\n- Build system (test, build, push)\n    - Quality gates: testing, test coverage, linting\n    - Security gates: immutable artifact (deployable image), security image scans\n- Rollout system \n   - Fetch the image and deploy\n   - Progressive (test, then promote production). Canary\n   - Multi-region","version":594,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"#ffffff","index":"bn0","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Requirements\n- Engineers want to ship their code to production (building, testing, deploying)\n- Build system (test, build, push)\n    - Quality gates: testing, test coverage, linting\n    - Security gates: immutable artifact (deployable image), security image scans\n- Rollout system \n   - Fetch the image and deploy\n   - Progressive (test, then promote production). Canary\n   - Multi-region","height":315,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1