. Build image only once\n- Deploy system: deploy code\n\n- Hot-fix deployments\n- Safe rollout, progressive rollout & canary\n- Automatic rollback\n- Multi-region deployments\n- Autoscaling of the platform, and absorb massive spikes\n- Observability and metrics of the platform.\n- Self remediation. If the pipelines are too slow, how observe and self-remediate. Survive production chaos\n- Guarantee non-bypassable guardrails\n- Network isolation, it must be able to deploy in other private k8s cluster (no public ips), draw security network boundaries, isolate team A from team B\n- RBAC\n- 3 layer approach: Interface plane, Control plane (validate schema & generate templates, handle persistent state management), Data plane\n","version":84,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"boS","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Functional Requirements\n\n\n- Engineer must be able to ship their code\n- Quality gateway: testing, linting, test coverage, SLOs for rollout\n- Security gateway: image scanning, immutable images, non-bypassable guardrails (compliance)\n- Build system: build code & generate artifacts. Build image only once\n- Deploy system: deploy code\n\n- Hot-fix deployments\n- Safe rollout, progressive rollout & canary\n- Automatic rollback\n- Multi-region deployments\n- Autoscaling of the platform, and absorb massive spikes\n- Observability and metrics of the platform.\n- Self remediation. If the pipelines are too slow, how observe and self-remediate. Survive production chaos\n- Guarantee non-bypassable guardrails\n- Network isolation, it must be able to deploy in other private k8s cluster (no public ips), draw security network boundaries, isolate team A from team B\n- RBAC\n- 3 layer approach: Interface plane, Control plane (validate schema & generate templates, handle persistent state management), Data plane\n","height":525,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":248029916,"